snippet: It was Sabine Lisicki’s turn to make tennis fans say, “Who?” by eliminating Serena Williams, who was fresh off dominating the French Open and had a 34-match winning streak.
abstract: Wimbledon Tennis Tournament has achieved some unusual milestones--fewest top-10 men and women in the third round, most retirements and withdrawals, most players over age 30 in the fourth round and no American men in the third round for the first time since 1912; Serena Williams, who was fresh off dominating the French Open and had a 34-match winning streak, is latest top player to fail to make the quarterfinals.
lead_paragraph: It was Sabine Lisicki’s turn to make tennis fans say, “Who?” by eliminating Serena Williams, who was fresh off dominating the French Open and had a 34-match winning streak.

headline.main: A Wimbledon of Falling Stars and Teardrops
headline.print_headline: One More Upset at a Tournament Full of Them
